options.content:
# Info
All values are averages based on a minimum interval of $inter. The minimum interval can be selected in dropdown box "Minimum Interval".

CPU Utilization and System Load are based on metrics collected from the database selected in the dropdown field. Origin is env_get_system_resources.

CPU Time per second panels are based on every database that shares the same hostname in the speedgain configuration with the database selected. Origin is mon_get_database.

panels.description: Server/Machine CPU Usage by all running procs

targets.rawSql:
select time,
cpu_user / (cpu_user+cpu_idle+cpu_iowait+cpu_system) as cpu_user,
cpu_iowait / (cpu_user+cpu_idle+cpu_iowait+cpu_system) as cpu_iowait,
cpu_system / (cpu_user+cpu_idle+cpu_iowait+cpu_system) as cpu_system
from (SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(snapshot_time,$__interval),
  (CASE WHEN avg(cpu_user) >= lag(avg(cpu_user)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) THEN avg(cpu_user) - lag(avg(cpu_user)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) WHEN lag(avg(cpu_user)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) IS NULL THEN NULL ELSE avg(cpu_user) END)/extract(epoch from min(snapshot_time) - lag(min(snapshot_time)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval))) AS "cpu_user",
  (CASE WHEN avg(cpu_idle) >= lag(avg(cpu_idle)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) THEN avg(cpu_idle) - lag(avg(cpu_idle)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) WHEN lag(avg(cpu_idle)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) IS NULL THEN NULL ELSE avg(cpu_idle) END)/extract(epoch from min(snapshot_time) - lag(min(snapshot_time)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval))) AS "cpu_idle",
  (CASE WHEN avg(cpu_iowait) >= lag(avg(cpu_iowait)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) THEN avg(cpu_iowait) - lag(avg(cpu_iowait)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) WHEN lag(avg(cpu_iowait)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) IS NULL THEN NULL ELSE avg(cpu_iowait) END)/extract(epoch from min(snapshot_time) - lag(min(snapshot_time)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval))) AS "cpu_iowait",
  (CASE WHEN avg(cpu_system) >= lag(avg(cpu_system)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) THEN avg(cpu_system) - lag(avg(cpu_system)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) WHEN lag(avg(cpu_system)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval)) IS NULL THEN NULL ELSE avg(cpu_system) END)/extract(epoch from min(snapshot_time) - lag(min(snapshot_time)) OVER (ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval))) AS "cpu_system"
FROM spg_mon_db2.v_env_get_system_resources
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(snapshot_time) AND
  display_name||member = '$datasource'
GROUP BY 1) as t
ORDER BY 1

panels.title: CPU Utilization

panels.description:
system load averages; short->1min, mid->5min, long->15min
Red dotted line is number of cores

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(snapshot_time,$__interval),
  avg(cpu_load_short) AS "load short",
  avg(cpu_load_medium) AS "load mid",
  avg(cpu_load_long) AS "load long",
  avg(cpu_total) AS "num cores"
FROM spg_mon_db2.v_env_get_system_resources
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(snapshot_time) AND
  display_name||member = '$datasource'
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY 1

panels.title: System Load

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  snapshot_time AS "time",
  *
FROM spg_mon_db2.v_env_get_system_resources
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(snapshot_time) AND
  display_name||member = '$datasource'
ORDER BY 1

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  $__timeGroupAlias(snapshot_time,$__interval,0),
  display_name AS metric,
  (CASE WHEN avg(total_cpu_time/1000) >= lag(avg(total_cpu_time/1000)) OVER (PARTITION BY display_name ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval,0)) THEN avg(total_cpu_time/1000) - lag(avg(total_cpu_time/1000)) OVER (PARTITION BY display_name ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval,0)) WHEN lag(avg(total_cpu_time/1000)) OVER (PARTITION BY display_name ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval,0)) IS NULL THEN NULL ELSE avg(total_cpu_time/1000) END)/extract(epoch from min(snapshot_time) - lag(min(snapshot_time)) OVER (PARTITION BY display_name ORDER BY $__timeGroup(snapshot_time,$__interval,0))) AS "Total Cpu Time"
FROM spg_mon_db2.v_mon_get_database
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(snapshot_time) AND
  hostname = (select distinct hostname from spg_mon_db2.v_mon_get_database where $__timeFilter(snapshot_time) and display_name||member='$datasource' fetch first 1 row only)
GROUP BY 1,2
ORDER BY 1,2

params: (select distinct hostname from spg_mon_db2.v_mon_get_database where $__timeFilter(snapshot_time) and display_name||member='$datasource' fetch first 1 row only)

list.definition:
select 
display_name||member as __value,display_name||'('||member||')'  as __text
from spg_mon_db2.v_v_display_name_member 
where bucket BETWEEN '${__from:date:YYYY-MM-DD}Z' and '${__to:date:YYYY-MM-DD}Z'
group by display_name,member
list.label: datasource
list.name: datasource
list.query:
select 
display_name||member as __value,display_name||'('||member||')'  as __text
from spg_mon_db2.v_v_display_name_member 
where bucket BETWEEN '${__from:date:YYYY-MM-DD}Z' and '${__to:date:YYYY-MM-DD}Z'
group by display_name,member
